news.title: Three-bedroom flat in Chandigarh sector 63 fetches Rs 1.5 crore in auction
news.para: Two other three-bedroom units in Sector 63 were sold for Rs 1.47 crore and Rs 1.38 crore against the same reserve price of Rs 1.12 crore. A total of 167 properties, both commercial and residential, were up for auction.

news.title: Kolkata: Bowbazar rebuild plan gets one bidder, families fear delay
news.para: A KMRC official had told TOI in October they wanted to start work by February 2023 so that the first lot of families could move in in 2025.

news.title: Gujarat assembly passes bill for regularising unauthorised constructions
news.para: Legislative and Parliamentary Affairs Minister Rushikesh Patel said a recent survey showed that nearly 42 per cent of buildings in eight major cities and 87 per cent of buildings in the jurisdiction of 156 municipalities did not have the mandatory "Building Use" or BU permission.

news.title: Property registrations drop in December in Maharashtra
news.para: Property registration department officials said the full-month registrations this December might not surpass the pre-pandemic level achieved for the same month in 2019, at 2.39 lakh.

news.title: Five farmhouses built in Aravalis demolished
news.para: "Notices were given last year to the owners of these farmhouses. We will carry out more such drives in the coming days to remove all encroachments from Aravali areas,” said Rajeev Ranjan, divisional forest officer, Gurgaon.

news.title: NCLT rejects Yes Bank's claim against Vijay Group Realty
news.para: The bank had moved the dedicated bankruptcy court against the company's insolvency resolution professional's decision to reject the claim and not include the bank in the committee of creditors (CoC).

news.title: Sebi to put in place governance norms for REITs, InvITs similar to listed companies
news.para: With respect to REITs and InvITs, the provisions such as those related to tenure of auditor, computation of leverage and unclaimed/unpaid distribution will be streamlined by the regulator.

news.title: Mindspace REIT raises Rs 100 crore through commercial papers
news.para: The funds will be utilised towards the working capital requirements of Mindspace REIT’s asset SPVs. The commercial papers are rated CRISIL A1+ by CRISIL.

news.title: U.S. home builder gloom persists, but some hope seen for next year
news.para: Interest rates on the most popular type of U.S. home loan topped 7% - the highest since 2001 - in October, and sales of new and existing homes tumbled by more than 30% from January through October.

news.title: Visaka Industries' new Rs 130-crore plant in West Bengal to be operational by Aug 2023
news.para: The project will raise the total capacity of environment-friendly boards and panels to 3.5 lakh tonne, a company official said. This will be Visaka's fifth cement fibre board plant in the country, and the first such unit in the eastern state.

news.title: Jaipur: JDA's Heritage City project paves way for Harigarh township on Agra Road
news.para: Almost declared as vested, the Harigarh project has generated as huge response since the Heritage Pink City project was announced in September.

news.title: Punjab government opens first sales centre for sand, gravel in Mohali
news.para: Bains pointed out that middlemen who are into storage of building material and some transporters were creating scarcity of the construction material and selling it at Rs 60 to 80 per cubic feet.

news.title: HC seeks 'specific details' of illegal construction in Aravalis
news.para: The matter is pending before the HC in the wake of a petition seeking directions to ban construction in Aravalli Hills by defining it as a forest area. The matter is pending before the HC since May 2018.

news.title: Stakeholders seek Mysuru civic body to expand tax net during pre-budget meeting
news.para: They put forward many such suggestions during the first pre-budget consultations meeting 2023-24, chaired by Mayor Shivakumar, held at Jayachamarajendra Wadiyar Meeting Hall on MCC office premises in the city.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body set to bring 2.4 lakh houses under tax ambit
news.para: With this, the cash-strapped municipal body hopes to generate an additional Rs 100 crore by the end of the 2022-23 fiscal.
